ems are outlined. I then predict a new effect, TDV, which solves\nthese problems, making exomoon detection viable. Chapter 7 presents a\nfeasibility study for detecting habitable-zone exomoons with Kepler, where it\nis found that moons down to 0.2 Earth masses are detectable. Finally,\nconclusions and future work are discussed in Chapter 8.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 May 2011 20:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2011 16:23:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Apr 2012 22:01:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-19"}
