nerate upstream magnetic turbulence at short\nand, by diffusive re-coupling, also long wavelengths in nearly parallel\nmagnetic field shocks; (ix) advection of such large-amplitude waves should\ncause periodic reformation of the quasi-parallel shock and eject large\namplitude magnetic field vortices downstream where they contribute to\nturbulence and to maintaining an extended region of large magnetic fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 May 2011 21:13:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 18 Jun 2011 16:38:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-10-20"}
